ROA is calculated using the formula:
ROA = Net Profit / Average Total Assets

Step 2: Calculate the Average Total Assets

Average Total Assets = (Initial Assets + Ending Assets) / 2
Average Total Assets = ($13,000,000.00 + $14,066,175.95) / 2
Average Total Assets = $27,066,175.95 / 2
Average Total Assets = $13,533,087.98

Step 3: Calculate ROA
ROA = Net Profit / Average Total Assets
ROA = -$1,669,849.77 / $13,533,087.98

Therefore, the Return on Assets (ROA) for this company is -12.34%.
